  "response": "No, alcohol consumption is not allowed on Indian Railways trains or within railway premises. Carrying alcohol on trains can also be subject to state regulations, as India has different alcohol laws depending on the state. Some states in India are completely dry, and carrying alcohol into these states could lead to legal consequences. It's always best to be cautious and adhere to local laws when traveling.",
